result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: The Court orders the defendant to reimburse Jefferson County for Court apppointed attorney fees in the amount of $1,112.47
with attachments and proposed order for payment of court appointed defense counsel fees from Attorney Samantha Humes in the amount of $1112.47

Cases 15CF108 & 15CM398 called together at 10:54 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Cameron J. Strese in court with Attorney Samantha Jeanne Humes. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
State files AMENDED information; Service of AMENDED information admitted; reading waived
Atty Humes submits letters in support of defendant along with plea paperwork

Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Counts #1, #2 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Case 15CM398
ADA Hall informs the Court that there is no victim impact statement or restitution request in either case

On Count #1, the Court IMPOSES AND STAYS 6 MONTHS JAIL, CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE, WITH HUBER ((Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of the jail term with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in system;  non-compliance will result in loss of Huber/Work-Release privileges without further process.) and places the Defendant on probation for 2 years, concurrent, with conditions:

On Counts #2 & #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 2 years, each count, concurrent, with conditions:
--Maintain absolute sobriety
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--No possession or consumption of alcohol or illegal drugs
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--Random drug and/or alcohol screening
--To undergo any other type of assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program or combination of the two, per Agent
--Anger Management counseling, per Agent
--To pay statutory costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including DNA Surcharges
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--To reimburse attorney fees
--No contact with Kalan Evans or William Kaplan
APPLY CASH BOND

Days credit for time already served: 1 day
Court does not authorize expungement
Recess: 11:21 am
